    "title": "LESSON 34: RELATIVE CLAUSES",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "Relative clauses add extra information:",
          "",
          "ENGLISH: The friend WHO helps me...",
          "GERMAN:  Der Freund, der mir hilft...",
          "",
          "Use der/die/das as 'who/which/that':",
          "",
          "der - masculine (Der Freund, der...)",
          "die - feminine (Die Freundin, die...)",
          "die - plural (Die Freunde, die...)",
          "",
          "If it's the OBJECT, use 'den' for masculine:",
          "",
          "Der Mann, den ich sehe, ist mein Lehrer.",
          "(The man that I see is my teacher)",
          "",
          "Relative clauses begin after a comma.",
          "They have a verb in the final position."
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 34"
      }
    ]
  },
