    "title": "LESSON 32: KENNEN VS WISSEN",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "Three different ways to say \"know\" in German:",
          "",
          "KENNEN = know (people, places, things)",
          "Ich kenne Berlin. (I know Berlin)",
          "Ich kenne sie. (I know her)",
          "Regular conjugation: kenne, kennst, kennt",
          "",
          "WISSEN = know (facts, information)",
          "Ich weiß das. (I know that)",
          "Ich weiß, dass... (I know that...)",
          "Irregular: ich weiß, du weißt, er weiß",
          "",
          "KÖNNEN = know how to (skill)",
          "Ich kann Deutsch. (I know/can speak German)",
          "Ich kann schwimmen. (I know how to swim)",
          "",
          "\"kennen\" is to be familiar with",
          "\"wissen\" is to know a fact"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 32"
      }
    ]
  }
]
